sql:
SELECT MAX(word_count) AS MaxWords
FROM (
  SELECT contributor_id, COUNT(word_id) AS word_count
  FROM words
  GROUP BY contributor_id
) AS contributor_word_counts;

external_knowledge:
- "sowers" refers to the contributors;
- "fruits of their labor" metaphorically represents the words and reviews;
- "seeds they planted" refers to the words contributed by the contributors;
- "echoes" represent the reviews on the words;
- "sweetness" symbolizes the rating given to the words;
- The garden metaphor represents the database or the community of words and phrases.

- Well-received terms typically have a rating greater than 3; 
- Terms without ratings are also considered as they may be new or less recognized;
- Popularity is gauged by the rating given to each term, with higher ratings indicating greater popularity;
- Categorization refers to the tag associated with each term, which may provide insight into its usage or context.

